{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"body":"DECISION: implement Fix #1 (gate era-verify when require_authenticated off) + Fix #4 (thread the already-built batched position/commit maps into verify_authorship_at_commit -> keys_valid_at_anchor so each event's era-check is O(1) git-map-lookup instead of a full-history git log per keyring record). Fix #4 is behavior-preserving (same introducing commit resolved, just via the batched map) and fixes whole-store cost regardless of window size. Dropping Fix #3 (--base windowing) — it decays and touches enforcement scope. Fix #2 already landed."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784391428487196001,"uuid":"292ec1ba-b993-4060-858b-962b0966a069"}